'''''Próxima Estación: Esperanza''''' is an album by [[Manu Chao]].  It was released in [[Europe]] in 2000. It was released in the [[United States]] on June 5, 2001 on [[Virgin Records]].  Chao and others sing in [[Arabic language|Arabic]], [[English language|English]], [[French language|French]], [[Galician language|Galician]], [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]], and [[Spanish language|Spanish]] on this album.

The name comes from a sample of an announcement for the [[:es:Estación de Esperanza|Esperanza]] [[List of Madrid metro stations|Madrid Metro station]], because in [[spanish language|Spanish]] [[Esperanza]] means "hope". The [[voice acting|voice actor]] Javier Dotú and a Metro announcer later sued for infringement of intellectual copyright over the use of their voices. <ref name="El mundo">{{cite news| author=EFE | title=Un actor y una locutora del Metro demandan a Manu Chao por derechos de propiedad intelectual | url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2002/11/16/cultura/1037447747.html | work=El Mundo | publisher=Pedro J. Ramírez | date=2002-11-18 | accessdate=2007-11-11 }}</ref>
